üìçRome by night  Rome at night is a magical city with beautifully illuminated monuments like the Colosseum and St. Peter's Basilica, creating an entirely new atmosphere. The daytime crowds give way to serene tranquility, allowing you to explore the city in peace. Many bars and restaurants stay open late, letting you enjoy the local cuisine and vibrant atmosphere. Evening markets and street musicians add a unique charm to the nighttime experience.
